      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HE IS THE KISS (7) finds the maiden win elusive (to say the least) but has been freshened with 59 days after finishing fifth over 1650m at Doomben in a tougher race. Best form is good enough so worth another chance. LUCKY ME (5) got a long way back before finishing sixth over a similar trip at Nowra last start, a less impressive effort than her fifth at Beaumont (Newcastle) the run before. Has been kept fresh for this and this looks easier, so can play a big role. REVA'S CHOICE (9) disappointed last time but was good two back at Dalby when finishing in the frame. Can sneak a minor spot if on song. HALLOWEEN HOLLY (4) is on debut. Trial form only moderate and she is likely to need the run, but monitor any market confidence.",
